1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,290
We aimlessly drift through the day, glad when it's finally over.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,290
But when we face the day with a plan, we get things done.

3
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:12,369
This common experience provides an important lesson.

4
00:00:12,480 --> 00:00:16,770
To accomplish something, we must plan to accomplish something.

5
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:23,570
Before World War II, our scientists saw the potential power locked in the atom.

6
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:29,570
but relatively little was known about how to split the atom and unleash that tremendous power.

7
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:37,010
When the United States entered the war, forward-thinking scientists saw the potential power of an atomic bomb.

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:43,089
A crash program was developed to accomplish just one goal, build an atomic bomb.

9
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,930
The result is history.

10
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:48,690
In just a few years, the concentrated effort paid off.

11
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,810
The bombs were dropped and the war was ended.

12
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:58,609
But without that crash program to accomplish a goal, splitting the atom would have been delayed perhaps a decade,

13
00:00:58,640 --> 00:00:59,810
maybe longer.

14
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:13,970
Set Goals to Get Things Done Our great production system would be hopelessly bogged down if production executives did not establish and adhere to target dates and production schedules.

15
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:20,930
Sales executives know salesmen sell more when they are given a carefully defined quota to sell.

16
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:26,770
Professors know students get term papers written on time when a deadline is set.

17
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:35,570
Now, as you press forward to success, set goals, deadlines, target dates, self-imposed quotas.

18
00:01:35,839 --> 00:01:39,649
You will accomplish only what you plan to accomplish.

19
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:46,369
According to Dr. George E. Birch of the Tulane University School of Medicine,

20
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:52,129
an expert in the study of human longevity, many things determine how long you will live.

21
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:56,690
Weight, heredity, diet, psychic tension, personal habits.

22
00:01:56,880 --> 00:02:02,369
But Dr. Birch says, the quickest way to the end is to retire and do nothing.

23
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:07,250
Every human being must keep an interest in life just to keep living.

24
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,730
Each of us has a choice.

25
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,010
Retirement can be the beginning or the end.

26
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:20,690
The do-nothing-but-eat-sleep-and-rock attitude is the poison-yourself-fast form of retirement.

27
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:28,770
Most folks who regard retirement as the end of purposeful living soon find retirement is the end of life itself.

28
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:33,649
With nothing to live for, no goals, people waste away fast.

29
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:41,890
The other extreme, the sensible way to retire, is the I'm-going-to-pitch-ride-in-and-start-fast method.
